&lt;h2 id="abi"&gt;ABI&lt;a class="anchor" href="#abi"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ABI - Application Binary Interface is a type of convetion for function calls, similar to how there is for syscalls.
The ABI that linux uses is called - &lt;strong&gt;System V ABI&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>